@@ -0,0 +1,91 @@
+===============================================================================
+IMPLEMENTATION: Show Play Buttons on Cards with Audio Preference
+===============================================================================
+
+ISSUE: Anki Desktop has a "Show play buttons on cards with audio" feature,
+       but AnkiDroid doesn't have it.
+
+SOLUTION: Added the preference to AnkiDroid with the same functionality.
+
+===============================================================================
+FILES MODIFIED
+===============================================================================
+
+1. AnkiDroid/src/main/res/values/10-preferences.xml
+   - Added: show_audio_play_buttons string (line 184)
+   - Added: show_audio_play_buttons_summ string (line 185)
+   - Fixed: pref_cat_fonts missing string (line 42)
+
+2. AnkiDroid/src/main/res/xml/preferences_appearance.xml
+   - Updated: SwitchPreferenceCompat for show_audio_play_buttons (lines 113-118)
+   - Changed from tools:title to proper android:title and android:summary
+
+3. AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/cardviewer/HtmlGenerator.kt
+   - Modified constructor to accept showAudioPlayButtons parameter (line 37)
+   - Modified createInstance() to read preference from SharedPreferences (line 64)
+   - Modified expandSounds() to pass preference value (line 53)
+
+4. AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/libanki/Sound.kt
+   - Modified expandSounds() to accept showPlayButtons parameter (line 228)
+   - Added conditional logic: show buttons OR strip references (lines 229-233)
+
+5. AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/libanki/SoundKt.kt
+   - Fixed bug in stripAvRefs() parameter order (line 61)
+
+6. AnkiDroid/src/test/java/com/ichi2/anki/cardviewer/ShowAudioPlayButtonsTest.kt
+   - NEW FILE: Created comprehensive unit tests
+
+===============================================================================
+PREFERENCE DETAILS
+===============================================================================
+
+Key: showAudioPlayButtons
+Type: Boolean
+Default: true (show play buttons)
+Location: Settings → Appearance → Reviewer
+Title: "Show play buttons on cards with audio"
+Summary: "Display play buttons for audio on cards"
+
+===============================================================================
+IMPLEMENTATION LOGIC
+===============================================================================
+
+When preference is TRUE (default):
+  [anki:play:q:0] → <a class='replay-button'>...</a> (SVG play button)
+
+When preference is FALSE:
+  [anki:play:q:0] → (removed from content)
+
+Audio files remain accessible via gestures regardless of preference.
+
+===============================================================================
+BACKWARD COMPATIBILITY
+===============================================================================
+
+✓ Default value maintains existing behavior (show buttons)
+✓ Sound.expandSounds() has default parameter for backward compatibility
+✓ Existing callers of Sound.expandSounds() continue to work
+✓ No breaking changes to any existing functionality
+
+===============================================================================
+TESTING
+===============================================================================
+
+Unit tests created in ShowAudioPlayButtonsTest.kt:
+  ✓ testExpandSoundsWithPlayButtonsEnabled()
+  ✓ testExpandSoundsWithPlayButtonsDisabled()
+  ✓ testExpandSoundsDefaultBehavior()
+  ✓ testExpandSoundsWithMultipleAudioTags()
+
+===============================================================================
+ANKI DESKTOP COMPATIBILITY
+===============================================================================
+
+Anki Desktop Reference:
+  https://github.com/ankitects/anki/blob/e327195470824074465657f98bb0282c7c93a56e/qt/aqt/main.py#L587-L592
+
+Anki Desktop uses: hide_audio_play_buttons
+AnkiDroid uses: showAudioPlayButtons (inverted logic, same functionality)
+
+===============================================================================
+

diff --git a/FEATURE_COMPLETE.md b/FEATURE_COMPLETE.md
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/FEATURE_COMPLETE.md
@@ -0,0 +1,194 @@
+# Feature Implementation Complete: Show Play Buttons on Cards with Audio
+
+## Executive Summary
+
+Successfully implemented the "Show play buttons on cards with audio" preference in AnkiDroid, matching the functionality available in Anki Desktop. This feature allows users to control whether audio play buttons are displayed on flashcards.
+
+## Feature Description
+
+### What It Does
+- Adds a new preference toggle in Settings → Appearance → Reviewer
+- When **enabled** (default): Cards with audio show clickable SVG play buttons
+- When **disabled**: Audio play button UI is hidden (audio still accessible via gestures)
+
+### Why It's Needed
+- Anki Desktop has this feature but AnkiDroid was missing it
+- Some users prefer a cleaner card interface without visible play buttons
+- Matches cross-platform consistency with Anki Desktop
+
+## Implementation Details
+
+### Architecture
+
+```
+User Interface (Preferences)
+         ↓
+SharedPreferences Storage
+         ↓
+HtmlGenerator.createInstance()
+         ↓
+HtmlGenerator.expandSounds()
+         ↓
+Sound.expandSounds()
+         ↓
+addPlayIcons() OR stripAvRefs()
+```
+
+### Code Changes
+
+#### 1. Preference Definition
